-- Most Indian Stocks Advance on Monetary Easing Speculation
-- B y   S a n t a n u   C h a k r a b o r t y
-- 2012-05-29T10:22:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-29/most-indian-stocks-advance-on-monetary-easing-speculation.html
Most Indian stocks rose, tracking
Asian equities, amid speculation slowing economic growth may
prompt the central bank to cut  reserve requirements  for banks.  Tata Consultancy Services Ltd. (TCS)  and  Infosys Ltd. (INFO) , two of
 India â€™s biggest software exporters, added more than 1 percent
each.  Coal India Ltd. (COAL)  rose the most in a week after profit at
the largest producer of the fuel beat analysts forecasts.  The BSE India  Sensitive Index (SENSEX) , or Sensex, advanced 0.1
percent to 16,438.58, according to preliminary closing prices in
Mumbai, its highest level since May 9. About three stocks
advanced for two that slipped. The economy likely grew 6.7
percent in the year ended March 31, from 8.4 percent in the
previous 12 months, according to a Bloomberg survey before a May
31 report.  Brent crude  has fallen 15 percent since March,
reducing costs for a country that imports 80 percent of its oil  The  Reserve Bank of India  has reduced the amount of funds
lenders must set aside as reserves twice this year. Last month,
the bank cut its benchmark rate for the first time since 2009
while flagging price pressures from the currency and oil costs.
Inflation unexpectedly quickened to 7.23 percent in April.  To contact the reporter on this story:
